  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nStarting from quarkus version `3.3.x` the spans are exported using Vert.x based exporters. It is not possible to set Proxy on the Vert.x Http client used by these exporters (analog to `quarkus.rest-client.my-client.proxy-address`). \r\n\r\nExpected: Via `quarkus.otel.exporter.otlp.traces.proxy-address` it should be possible to configure a proxy server to be used to communicate with external server.\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\n1. Extend `OtlpExporterTracesConfig` with `proxyAddress` property.\r\n2. Extend `io.quarkus.opentelemetry.runtime.exporter.otlp.OTelExporterRecorder.HttpClientOptionsConsumer#HttpClientOptionsConsumer` with `proxyAddress` and add private method `configureProxy`\r\n\r\nWith the above proposed small changes, it will be possible to use these exporters behind a proxy\r\n\r\n\r\n_No response_",
